- Create a new release in GitHub
	- Tag: release-<version>
	- Title: <version>
	- Version examples: 0.1-rc1 0.1 0.1.1
	- Mark "rc" releases as pre-releases
- Wait for release workflow to attach the files
- Update and commit homebrew-safer
  - Download release .tar.gz
  - Get checksum: shasum -a 256 ...
  - Update:
    - sha256
    - version
    - url
  - Commit message: Release <version>
- Update and commit safer docs
  - sed -i 's/release-<old_version>/release-<version>/g' README.md web/index.html
  - Commit message: Update install instructions after release <version>
